## Post-release patch

**`/r-save` insights trim no longer stalls on `mv -i` alias.** Section 6
trimming previously used `tail -30 file > tmp && mv tmp file`, which
hung on interactive shells that alias `mv` to `mv -i` — the overwrite
prompt blocked the non-interactive Bash tool call. Replaced with an
in-place `sed -i "1,\$((lines-30))d"` edit that sidesteps the alias
entirely. No behavior change on fresh shells; fixes /r-save for users
whose shell rc sets the common `mv`/`cp`/`rm` interactive aliases.

**Plan schema rules extracted into a single source of truth.** The
Regression-case validation prose previously inlined in `/r-build`
Section 1 has been lifted into `canonical/reference/plan-schema.md`
(Plan-Version Awareness + Rules 1-7), and `/r-plan` gained a Step 2.7
that runs the same validation pass after writing the plan and before
reviewer dispatch. Three call sites — planner pre-reviewer pass,
reviewer challenge mode, and `/r-build` Section 1 — now apply the
same rules in the same order from the same file. Schema errors that
previously surfaced only at dispatch time (wrong category for pure
test-addition phases, whole-file invariant shorthand in Regression-case,
deferred CVE references) are caught while the author is still in the
planning loop. New rules (4c forbidden shapes, 6 category
disambiguation) codify the exact author mistakes observed in recent
sessions. No bash script — markdown-first by design, so the LLM keeps
judgment for genuine edge cases and a single edit to the schema doc
updates all three callers.
